cfonline access with authorization2star  aOur health system resembles a repair service which treats illness and suffering. But in many cases it would seem much simpler to avoid health problems. Why do we wait until the illnesses have developed? Young and expectant families are particularly interested in maintaining the health of their children and their whole family. Since prevention must begin long before the emergence of illness, there can be no better time to start than the beginning of life. This book presents a range of contributions that not only encourage theoretical reflection about the topics discussed but also provide practical suggestions.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aFamilie. 4aGesundheitserziehung. 4aGesundheitsvorsorge. 7aMEDICAL / General.2bisacsh1 aBecker, Sibylle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergmann, Karl E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergmann, Karl E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBergmann, Renate L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergmann, Renate L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDittmann, Sieghart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDudenhausen, Joachim W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFurian, Gerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGruber, Michaela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuber, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKahl, Heidrun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKamtsiuris, Panagiotis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 a